BaIrO$_{3}$ is a distorted perovskite which has a number of phase transitions with increasing pressure (Cheng, 2009; Cheng, 2013). 
 (Cheng, 2009) label the structures by the approximate stacking of the BaO$_{3}$ layers. \begin{itemize} \item 0-3 GPa: \href{current_web_home_dir/ABC3_mC60_12_3i_ac2i_3i3j-001}{the ground state $\alpha$-BaIrO$_{3}$} ``9R'' structure, in space group $C2/m$ \#12. (this structure) \item 3-5 GPa: \href{current_web_home_dir/ABC3_mC50_12_a2i_c2i_be2i2j-001}{$\beta$-BaIrO$_{3}$} ``5H'' structure, also in space group $C2/m$ \#12. \item 5-18 GPa: $\gamma$-BaIrO$_{3}$, which has the \href{current_web_home_dir/}{SrIrO$_{3}$} ``6H'' structure. \item 18-?? GPa:  $\delta$-BaIrO$_{3}$ is in the \href{current_web_home_dir/A3BC_tI20_140_ah_b_c-002}{tetragonal $\gamma$-SrZrO$_{3}$} structure. \item Presumably at some point above 25 GPa the compound transforms into the \href{current_web_home_dir/AB3C_cP5_221_a_c_b-001}{cubic perovskite ($E2_{1}$)} ``3C'' structure. \end{itemize} ~ \vspace{-.25in} 
 (Siegrist, 1991) put the second iridium atom at the (2d) Wyckoff position.  The AFLOW labeling standard moves this to the (2c) site.  This requires a new unit cell: Our $\bf{a}_{3}$ vector is equal to the sum of the (Siegrist, 1991) primitive cell vectors $\bf{a}_{1} + \bf{a}_{2} + \bf{a}_{3}$.
